(CNN) -- In her first televised appearance since Cory Monteith's death, Lea Michele took the stage at the Teen Choice Awards on Sunday night and dedicated her Choice TV Actress -- Comedy prize to her late "Glee" co-star and real-life boyfriend.

"I wanted to dedicate this award to Cory," she said while fighting back tears. "For all of you out there who loved and admired Cory as much as I did, I promise that, with your love, we're going to get through this together.

